          "number": 408,
          "state": "open",
          "state_reason": null,
          "title": "Sync check not correct",
          "body": "We currently check if the bitcoin chain has been synced like this: https://github.com/interlay/interbtc-clients/blob/e6ee91dbaf1d390fec205cd63e122dc87785b50f/bitcoin/src/lib.rs#L394\r\n\r\nHowever, neither `initial_block_download` nor `verification_progress` can be relied upon, see https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/issues/26432 and https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/issues/26433\r\n\r\nAccording to [stackexchange](https://bitcoin.stackexchange.com/questions/96452/how-to-detect-that-full-node-is-in-sync-using-jsonrpc) we should compare the `blocks` and `headers` fields - if they are equal then the bitcoin node is synced. \r\n\r\n",
